    "description": "Lilycolor Co., Ltd. plans, develops, and sells interior products in Japan.It offers wallpaper, curtain, and floor materials under the Lilycolor brand. The company is also involved in the provision of office space and facility interior design, construction, and project management; proposal and sale of furniture, partitions, and office supplies; real estate brokerage; and development, sale, value restoration, and rental and consulting activities for various real estate comprising condominiums, office buildings, commercial facilities, and accommodation and healthcare facilities. It sells its products to interior construction companies and specialty stores, upholstery stores, design offices, housing manufacturers, construction companies, and developers. The company was formerly known as Kawakichi Co., Ltd. and changed its name to Lilycolor Co., Ltd. in 1989. The company was founded in 1907 and is headquartered in Shinjuku, Japan."
